+- # ORC Format
+- ExternalProject_Add (orc-format_ep
+--  URL "https://archive.apache.org/dist/orc/orc-format-${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}/orc-format-${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}.tar.gz"
+--  URL_HASH SHA256=739fae5ff94b1f812b413077280361045bf92e510ef04b34a610e23a945d8cd5
+-+  URL "https://github.com/apache/orc-format/archive/v${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}.tar.gz"
+-+  DOWNLOAD_NAME "orc-format-${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}.tar.gz" 
+-+  URL_HASH SHA256=43E92BEDE65FDC7F56FD0C56A07F3FAD3E553C598A055534C36D86E17B69E1CE  CONFIGURE_COMMAND ""
+-   CONFIGURE_COMMAND ""
+-   BUILD_COMMAND     ""
+-   INSTALL_COMMAND     ""
+-
+```
+
+# How it works
+1. vcpkg will download orc pacakge accoring to command in unmodified file `/ci/vcpkg/overlayPorts/orc/portfile.cmake`:
+```
+vcpkg_from_github(
+  OUT_SOURCE_PATH SOURCE_PATH
+  REPO apache/orc
+  REF "v${VERSION}"
+  SHA512 6109b27047b0688566756f9ca6833689cdf0bd7a5086c4212ef1fd6484fb73d9077fa3017137a7fd65f0ab51518c80fc43ab55bd308ad146f6f4b6d97c51b4fc
+  HEAD_REF master
+  PATCHES
+    fix-cmake.patch
+)
+```
+2. The downloaded file (`orc-2.0.0.tar.gz`) contains a script: `orc-2.0.0/cmake_modules/ThirdpartyToolchain.cmake` which installs `orc`. Among other things this script has command which dowloads file:
+```
+ExternalProject_Add (orc-format_ep
+  URL "https://archive.apache.org/dist/orc/orc-format-${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}/orc-format-${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}.tar.gz"
+  URL_HASH SHA256=739fae5ff94b1f812b413077280361045bf92e510ef04b34a610e23a945d8cd5
+  CONFIGURE_COMMAND ""
+  BUILD_COMMAND     ""
+  INSTALL_COMMAND     ""
+  TEST_COMMAND     ""
+)
+```
+3. vcpkg patches `orc-2.0.0/cmake_modules/ThirdpartyToolchain.cmake` file wtih patch appended to list of patches in `ci/vcpkg/overlayPorts/orc/fix-cmake.patch` to make the command look like:
+```
+ExternalProject_Add (orc-format_ep
+  URL "https://github.com/apache/orc-format/archive/v${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}.tar.gz"
+  DOWNLOAD_NAME "orc-format-${ORC_FORMAT_VERSION}.tar.gz" 
+  URL_HASH SHA256=43E92BEDE65FDC7F56FD0C56A07F3FAD3E553C598A055534C36D86E17B69E1CE
+  CONFIGURE_COMMAND ""
+  BUILD_COMMAND     ""
+  INSTALL_COMMAND     ""
+  TEST_COMMAND     ""
+)
+```
+4. vcpkg/cmake execute patched 
+
+# Alternatives Considered
+Two alternatives considered to keep network isolation:
+1. Using terrapin retrieval ThirdpartyTool
+2. Using github archive
+
+## Terrapin Retrieval Tool
+### Documentation:
+https://eng.ms/docs/cloud-ai-platform/devdiv/one-engineering-system-1es/1es-docs/secure-supply-chain/oss-supply-chain-security/vcpkg#asset-caching--source-mirroring
+### Implementation for arrow 15:
+https://dev.azure.com/msazure/One/_git/Data-ThirdParty-Apache-Arrow?version=GTarrow15-terrapin
+
+### Main idea
+Fetch all the thirdparty artifacts using Terrapin command:
+```
